<div class="gm-screen-grid">

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Charge Weapon Firing</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Charge (X):</strong> is the amount of Half Actions needed before firing.</div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Automatic Rate of Fire</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Auto (X):</strong> is the amount of shots made in a Full Action.</div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Burst Fire</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Burst (X):</strong> is the amount of shots made in a Half Action. A single +10 To Hit is made and all can be Evaded all at once by the Target.</div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Flintlock Rate of Fire</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Flintlock:</strong> is a Full Action to fire one Attack.</div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Pump Action</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Pump (X):</strong> is the amount of shots made in a Half Action. A Reaction can be used once per Round to fire additional shot with -10 Reaction Penalty.</div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Semi-Automatic Rate of Fire</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Semi-Auto (X):</strong> is the amount of shots made in a Half Action with a +10 Bonus To Hit.</div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Sustained Rate of Fire</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Sustained (X):</strong> is the amount of shots made in a Full Action. Made using 1 To Hit Test, each Degree of Success adds an additional set of Damage to a maximum of (X).</div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="gm-panel">
    <h2>Drawback Rate of Fire</h2>
    <div class="gm-source-ref core">Ref: p.28</div>
    <div class="gm-callout">
      <div><strong>Drawback (X):</strong> is the amount of Half Actions it takes to pull back a weapon to fire it. Weapon fires at the final Half Action. Damage is halved for each Half Action ignored in (X).</div>
    </div>
  </article>

</div>